	   <tr><td colspan=2>Druids max at 175 in their melee skills, and advance at a max of (level+1) * 4 instead of the (level+1) * 5 formula of the Melee classes.&nbsp;&nbsp;INT casters advance at (level+1) * 3.  I assume clerics advance on the same lines as druids.<br><br>So at low levels, the difference in the 'To Hit' and damage numbers isn't that great.  This is quite significant at higher levels however.  At 51, it is quite rare that I can do much damage through melee, so I only use it if I'm soloing and only a tiny sliver of hps remains, not enough to waste mana on.  However, even if you can't hit a creature, a processing weapon can still go off on a miss.  This one appears to have a Right-Click effect though, which is much nicer.  If I were an INT caster, I would like to have this weapon.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
